If you mean &quot;when someone kills the process&quot; i think it wouldn&#39;t be possible, as the process ***gets killed*** and so stops its execution _immediately_. If you mean &quot;when the application freezes and the user forces it to close&quot; I think it wouldn&#39;t be possible too, usually if you force the quit of an application, it means that it&#39;s _frozen_ and it&#39;s _not responding anymore_, so executing other code of it wouldn&#39;t be possible.

